This paper deals with evolutionary algorithms for multi-objective optimization, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of computational intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of metrics and analysis of algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of specific optimization functions, which could relate to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
